e is one area where I believe I have been mislead.  <br>
<br>
I have been playing a warrior now for 12 levels, and I've got to say that it's a lot harder than I thought it would be!  So I started looking into the issue a little deeper.  Now I haven't climbed high enough in levels to really have a strong opinion on the matter, so take what I say with a grain of salt, but I gotta say that I'm not so offended by the melee upgrades any more.  I think the complaints of warrior just might have some merit.  I think the real issue is item inbalance and not class inbalance.  Sure my wizard felt useless next to a warrior hitting for big damage, and barely being scratched by the mobs we were fighting, while I spent all my time medding just trying to keep up.  However now that I've played a warrior I realize that the only reason this was the case was due to twinking.  As an un twinked warrior I get my butt handed to me on a regular basis.  <br>
<br>
I have no means of escape whatsoever, and it only gets worse at higher levels, when greens can give you a beat down too.  A green might be able to beat down a wizard too, but only if he's oom!  Otherwise root, and run, or gate, etc.  If you're a warrior, you either have a sow potion or you are SOL!  You can't run fast, you can't root, you can't gate, you can't do anything, but fight and hope you win, or run for zone, and hope you make it.  God forbid you die and have to cross a hostile zone.  You have no invis to hide, can't defend yourself, and you can't outrun anybody.  I'd rather be a dead wizard on a CR, than a warrior any day of the week!  In fact I'd rather be ANY other class on a CR than a warrior!  This goes for the whining hybrids as well!  I'm told they have only a few hundred less hp at high levels, and access to gear that is nearly equivalent in AC!  What's the point of giving up all those spells to be a warrior anyway?  Just so you can take one or two more hits before you die?  <br>
<br>
I've got quite a few levels to go, before I can pass judgement, but I have to say that I'm viewing the world of Norrath from a completely new perspective.  Anyone here complaining that wizards are underpowered compared to melee should walk in their shoes before they open their mouth.  Not saying you haven't, and you're certainly entitled to your opinion if you have, and still feel that way, but I'd be willing to bet that a good number of you haven't played a warrior, while denouncing them as over powered.  A warrior is his gear, and as we all know the best gear in this game isn't all that easy to get.  Wizards certainly have issues, and could use all the enhancements that I hope SOL will bring, but you won't catch me chiming in on the warriors should be nerfed crud any more!<br>
<br>
Please don't flame me for this, as I stated I haven't played either class to high levels, and claim to be anything but an authority on the matter.  However, I just wanted to point out that things aren't always what they seem, and we should all try to keep an open mind when it comes to addressing the complaints of each class. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwhizbangdustyboots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 2425<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/30/01 12:10 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My eyes have been opened!</span><hr size=1> Tanks definitely need magic items. Gate potions, jboots and inviz pots are all key. (It's a shame the inviz ring from Chardok is so limited in who can use it.)<br>
<br>
I'm not sure the answer is what VI thinks it is, though. Bigger and better weapons aren't the solution to everything. <p><a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=49189" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/whiz-banner-long.gif" height=60 width=468 alt="Whizbang Dustyboots" border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 3555<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/30/01 12:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My eyes have been opened!</span><hr size=1> Yes, Warriors are not all powerful and have weaknesses.  That doesn't really negate what's been said though, they have been enormously upgraded and Wizards have had no change over the same level range with each expansion.  Thus, there's a problem here, since most people (everyone who was there at the time at least) agree that Wizards and melee were pretty well balanced BEFORE the expansions.<br>
<br>
I play a Rogue, Warrior, and Paladin in addition to my Wizard (plus a bard), and believe me I know what they can do and can't do.  There's a world of difference, though. <p><IMG SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg" ></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utorcerarcana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Torcer Arcana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 449<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/30/01 12:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My eyes have been opened!</span><hr size=1>      I'm not sure why anyone would ever compare a Warrior w/o Eqp. with a Wizard w/o Eqp.  It makes more sense to compare the Wizard w/ Eqp to the Warrior w/ Eqp., since this will be the norm in the game world. <p>Torcer Arcana<Br>Level 55 Wizard<Br>The Nameless</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unatanmagus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Natan Magus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 615<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/30/01 12:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My eyes have been opened!</span><hr size=1> &quot;Now I haven't climbed high enough in levels to really have a strong opinion on the matter, so take what I say with a grain of salt, but I gotta say that I'm not so offended by the melee upgrades any more. I think the complaints of warrior just might have some merit.&quot;<br>
