On the flip side, take a lvl 50 warrior and a lvl 50 wizard into Sollusek A, I think you will find the wizard having lots of problems from greens, but not the warrior. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unatanmagus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Natan Magus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 618<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/30/01 12:30 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My eyes have been opened!</span><hr size=1> It really depends on the server.<br>
<br>
On Mith Marr (one of the older servers) you really don't meet an untwinked low level Meleer.<br>
Most Meleers are heavily twinked. And heavily twinked does not mean Ykeshas. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 3558<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/30/01 12:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My eyes have been opened!</span><hr size=1> So would you say that a tank that twinks with gear that your level 27 Wizard can get in those places would be no more effective than the Wizard?  That the effect of this gear on the tank would be not more than the Wizard?  You and I both know that is absurd.  The effect of equivalent level items on a Wizard as on a melee class is tremendously different.  Slapping a high damage low delay weapon in a level 1 Warrior's hand will make him instantly rip things up horribly, a Wizard cannot use these weapons (anything that might be like that for a caster is no drop), and their spells will never, ever, EVER do more than their set formula under any circumstances, no matter what gear you put on them.<br>
<br>
Further, you can try to equal a melee class' AC and even hit points, and you STILL won't be as safe as they are because of several factors.  <br>
1) Wizards don't even HAVE dodge until level 22, melee get it in the first 10 levels.<br>
2) Wizards get 3 points of defense per level, melee get 5, with warriors an additional 5 points.<br>
3) Warriors get Parry at level 10 and Riposte at level 25, neither of which a Wizard has.<br>
4) Try to put a flowing thought item on a level 27 Wizard.  Now choose any one of the many hp regen items out there for the Warrior types, few of which a Wizard can even wear.<br>
<br>
I understand what you are trying to say, but I see you again and again trying to downplay the effect of twinking in the game, as if you can twink a caster as effectively, easily, and cheaply as you can a melee class.  And that's patently false. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarmok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Armok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 311<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/30/01 12:47 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My eyes have been opened!</span><hr size=1> At the low levels, warriors are nicely balanced against casters given level appropriate gear.  Up to level 10, a warrior with rusty weapons and leather armor is going to have a rough go of it, and will still suffer wipeouts when grouped from time to time.<br>
<br>
However, on older servers, any player that has a clue can self twink from scratch with little trouble. Higher level players, flush with cash, pay a premium for items lower level characters naturally harvest (bat wings, bone chips, and spider silks). On new servers, players just don't have a chance to acquire cash like they do on older servers.  The second part of the equation is the falling prices of highly available weapons in the level 40 range.  You can easily find a Frozen Longsword (7/26, magic 1hs) or it's equivalent for sale in the 20-50p range from other players.  Compare this to a rusty longsword at 5/35.  That's roughly double the damage output.<br>
<br>
There is simply no equivalent for a caster.  Yes, you can twink out a caster heavily to make him a decent tank at the early levels, but you can always twink out a tank better with equivalent funds.<br>
<br>
